HEADWORD: Aretaics
<hw>Ar`e*ta"ics</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
virtue.]</ety> <def>The ethical theory which excludes all relations
between virtue and happiness; the science of virtue; -- contrasted with
<xex>eudemonics</xex>.</def> <rj><au>J. Grote.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
